dcterms:description: The pendulum dataset consists of pairs of images that represent the location and velocity of a pendulum. The learned equivariant embedding encodes both the location and velocity, with transformations applied in the form of positive or negative torque.
dcterms:title: Pendulum Dataset

dcterms:description: The mountain car dataset consists of pairs of images that represent two consecutive frames of a car in a mountainous environment. The learned embedding captures both the location and velocity of the car, with transformations applied through a range of accelerations.
dcterms:title: Mountain Car Dataset

dcterms:description: The rotating chair dataset involves a 3D chair that is transformed through the action of the group SO(3). The dataset captures the rotations of the chair and visualizes the latent embedding corresponding to these transformations.
dcterms:title: Rotating Chair Dataset

dcterms:description: The double-bump world dataset consists of a rectangular bump signal and a triangular bump signal that have been cyclically shifted and superimposed. The dataset captures transformations of these bumps and learns to represent their locations.
dcterms:title: Double-Bump World Dataset

dcterms:description: The Gym Mini-world dataset consists of first-person views of a 3D room containing various colored boxes. The dataset captures transformations including rotations and movements of the agent within the environment.
dcterms:title: Gym Mini-world Dataset

dcterms:description: The Atari Games dataset includes environments such as Pong and Space Invaders. The dataset is used to evaluate the performance of the learned representations in reinforcement learning tasks.
dcterms:title: Atari Games (Pong and Space Invaders)

dcterms:description: The Inverted Pendulum, Reacher, and Swimmer datasets consist of environments used in reinforcement learning tasks. These datasets capture the dynamics of the respective environments and are used to evaluate the learned representations.
dcterms:title: Inverted Pendulum, Reacher, and Swimmer Datasets
